 The Minister of Health, Osagie Ehanire, has debunked the rumour that the Chief of Staff to the President, Abba Kyari, might have been moved out of the country for proper treatment of Coronavirus. He said this during a chat with Channels TV on Politics Today on Sunday night, shortly after President Muhammadu Buhari’s nationwide broadcast. He was responding to a question asking him to confirm or dismiss insinuations that one of the close aides of the President, who had tested positive with the virus, was currently outside the country for its treatment. “To my knowledge, nobody has left the country for treatment of coronavirus. No country will even be willing to accept any case at this time. The capacities here have been expanding.
We’ve had donations of space and facilities that can be used effectively,” the minister said. Update later… 